Systems that have been found to perform well on UNIPEN include a writerindependent approach based on hidden Markov models (HMMs) [7]; a hybrid technique called cluster generative statistical dynamic time warping [8], which combines dynamic time warping with HMMs and embeds clustering and statistical sequence modeling in a single feature space;
and a support vector machine with a novel Gaussian
dynamic time warping kernel [9].

